name: First step in building a sustainable tech community
description: The event will be the official launching of GDG ogbomoso where developers meet, network, collaborate and learn. Its targeted to help build a strong tech community amongst developers and designers in Ogbomoso, and also to bring in tech enthusiasts into a community where they can find a strong support for their chosen path in tech. This event features codelabs on web and mobile technologies, talks on demystifying machine learning, artificial intelligence and data science and many more.

name: IWD Ogbomoso
description:
Women TechMakers(WTM) Lautech

Among the amazing opportunities that comes with the WTM communities is the International Womens Day(IWD) Celebrations.

Celebrating the women in STEM and beyond, WTM Communities from all over the world are continuously holding incredible events to provide an opportunity for their communities to have an experience of the IWD Summits that are held in various countries all over the world.

Join Women Techmakers Lautech as they hold an amazing meetup on 23rd March 2019 as the extended version of the one that will be holding in Lagos on the 16th of March,2019.

Tell a friend and come for inspirational talks, hands on codelabs, icebreakers, access to amazing communication building workshops and a customized networking experience.

We can't wait to see you there!

What to bring:
-Your Laptop and internet
-A notebook and a Pen
-Excitement
-A friend!!!

You can join our whatsapp group https://chat.whatsapp.com/JHfqi5xfML4HB4ce4qzF1p

Note:
The event is welcome to all.

name: Cloud Study Jam 2019 - Baseline: ML, Data, AI
description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!
Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console and Machine Learning.
Then after our live session, you will have free access to more labs you can finish at home. Complete all labs in the quest and earn a Google-hosted badge for your online profile, and additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want.

What to bring:
- Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! with the latest Firefox or Chrome installed
- Extension Boxes
- Internet
- Snacks

Don't forget your charger.
